hallenges in the 2020s—and would do well to learn from each other’s strengths. This book discusses the new dimensions of competition that will affect corporate strategy in the next decade and how leaders can reinvent their organizations to be better suited for the new environment. The companies that succeed in the 2020s will look very different than they do today—they will have evolved their businesses to harness new technologies and reshaped their external relationships, organizations, and approaches accordingly. Winning the ’20s will help business professionals as well as academics and students with an interest in strategy and leadership answer this critical question for the start of this decade: How should you prepare your company to avoid being left behind and emerge as a winner in a rapidly evolving business landscape?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Leadership.2bisacsh1 aBailey, Allison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBürkner, Hans-Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChittaro, Claudio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFæste, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHutchinson, Rich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrentz, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLesser, Rich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLotan, Hen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNanda, Saumeet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReeves, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReeves, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTsusaka, Miki, ec